Abstract
Vehicle Number Plate Detection is an automated system developed using Python to identify and extract vehicle registration numbers from images. The main aim of this project is to reduce manual effort and improve efficiency in vehicle identification processes. This system uses image processing techniques along with Optical Character Recognition (OCR) to detect and recognize number plates.
The project is implemented using Python libraries such as OpenCV, NumPy, and Tesseract OCR. Initially, the input image is preprocessed by converting it into grayscale and removing noise. Edge detection and contour detection methods are applied to locate the number plate region. Once the number plate is identified, it is extracted from the image and passed to the OCR engine, which converts the image into readable text.This system can be applied in various real-world scenarios such as traffic monitoring, parking systems, toll collection, and security applications. The project demonstrates how computer vision and machine learning techniques can be used to build intelligent systems. It is simple, efficient, and suitable for beginners in AI and ML.

📘 Introduction

In recent years, the number of vehicles on the road has increased rapidly, leading to challenges in traffic management, law enforcement, and security monitoring. Manual identification of vehicle number plates is time-consuming and prone to errors. Therefore, there is a need for an automated system that can quickly and accurately detect vehicle registration numbers.Vehicle Number Plate Detection is a computer vision-based application that helps in identifying and extracting number plates from images or video streams. This project focuses on developing a system using Python that can detect the number plate region and recognize the characters present on it.
The system uses OpenCV for image processing tasks such as grayscale conversion, noise reduction, edge detection, and contour detection. These techniques help in locating the number plate area in the image. After detecting the number plate, Tesseract OCR is used to extract the text from the image.A simple web interface is developed using Flask, where users can upload vehicle images and get the detected number plate as output. This makes the system user-friendly and easy to use.
This project is useful in real-time applications like automated toll booths, parking management systems, traffic rule enforcement, and surveillance systems. It also provides a strong foundation for understanding image processing and OCR techniques in artificial intelligence.📘
